{"id":1012,"date":"2022-02-04T16:23:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-04T16:23:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1012"},"modified":"2022-02-02T15:21:06","modified_gmt":"2022-02-02T15:21:06","slug":"configure-systems-to-mount-file-systems-at-boot-by-universally-unique-id-uuid-or-label","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1012","title":{"rendered":"Configure systems to mount file systems at boot by universally unique ID (UUID) or label"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When we successfully create logical volume and formatted it, as the last thing we need to mount it to some file system. Without this step, the logical volume is just empty space pointing to nowhere.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To mount logical volume, we use &#8220;mount command&#8221; (you didn&#8217;t see that coming, huh!)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"temporary-mounting\">Temporary mounting<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;m specifically saying temporary because this method won&#8217;t survive reboot, which is the necessary point in RHCSA exam.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To mount something, we first need to know what are we going to mount and where. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Use lvdisplay to find out what<\/strong> (you obviously need to create logical volume first)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"303\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?resize=640%2C303&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1013\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?w=676&amp;ssl=1 676w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?resize=300%2C142&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-241.png?resize=48%2C23&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And where to mount it, is a question of making a file system<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">mkdir \/mnt\/path_to_mount<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"447\" height=\"43\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?resize=447%2C43&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1014\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?w=447&amp;ssl=1 447w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?resize=300%2C29&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-242.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 447px) 100vw, 447px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we simply join these two things together.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"583\" height=\"284\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?resize=583%2C284&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1018\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?w=583&amp;ssl=1 583w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?resize=300%2C146&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?resize=24%2C12&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?resize=36%2C18&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-244.png?resize=48%2C23&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 583px) 100vw, 583px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"permanently-mounting-a-file-system\">Permanently mounting a file system<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"using-uuid\">USING UUID<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To permanently mount a filesystem we use a file \/etc\/fstab . Which holds static information about all the mounts. This file is used in a boot process, so your mount survives downtimes, reboot etc&#8230;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/etc\/fstab<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"181\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=640%2C181&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1021\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?w=861&amp;ssl=1 861w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=300%2C85&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=768%2C217&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image.png?resize=48%2C14&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>There are multiple ways to mount a file system. The most used one and preferred one is using UUID, which is specific code that only this file system has. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get this UUID you have to type the command below and find your file system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">blkid<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"120\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=640%2C120&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1022\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?w=916&amp;ssl=1 916w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=300%2C56&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=768%2C144&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-1.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><br>And we just need to get this UUID code to the fstab file, so let&#8217;s reopen fstab<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/etc\/fstab<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>There is a trick to be able to copy path or UUID without using two terminals. It&#8217;s prety handy so I&#8217;ll show you. <\/p><p>Simply type inside vi this command<\/p><p>:r !blkid<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will past the output of the blkid command into your vi opened file, and you can simply delete the unnecessary stuff.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the end, it should look like this. (depending on the format and mount name you used, ofc). <a href=\"https:\/\/geek-university.com\/linux\/etc-fstab-file\/\">Here<\/a> you can find explanation of every value in the command.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"197\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=640%2C197&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1023\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?w=860&amp;ssl=1 860w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=300%2C92&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=768%2C237&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-2.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Save and close the file and as the last thing to check if everything is corrected we can remount all mount written in fstab by typing<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">mount -a <\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"558\" height=\"289\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?resize=558%2C289&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?w=558&amp;ssl=1 558w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?resize=300%2C155&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?resize=24%2C12&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-3.png?resize=48%2C25&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And as you can see, it&#8217;s still mounted, good job! *Virtual high five*<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"using-a-label\">Using a label<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"labeling-xfs\">Labeling xfs<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;ve created another logical volume from disk \/dev\/sdb1 with ext formatting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"292\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?resize=640%2C292&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1033\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?w=652&amp;ssl=1 652w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-6.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"548\" height=\"35\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?resize=548%2C35&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1036\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?w=548&amp;ssl=1 548w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?resize=300%2C19&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?resize=36%2C2&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-9.png?resize=48%2C3&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 548px) 100vw, 548px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"23\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=640%2C23&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1035\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?w=995&amp;ssl=1 995w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=300%2C11&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=768%2C27&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=24%2C1&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=36%2C1&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-8.png?resize=48%2C2&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For efs filesystem we use xfs_admin command to add a label to the logical volume<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">xfs_admin -L LABEL path_to_logical_volume<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"77\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?resize=640%2C77&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1037\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?w=655&amp;ssl=1 655w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?resize=300%2C36&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-10.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"labeling-ext4\">Labeling ext4<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is pretty much the same thing, except we use a different command to do it<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>tune2fs -L<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"mounting-a-labeled-filesystem\">Mounting a labeled filesystem<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When we&#8217;ve successfully labeled our file system, it&#8217;s time to add this to the fstab file. But before that, create a file to mount it to<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"418\" height=\"35\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?resize=418%2C35&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1038\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?w=418&amp;ssl=1 418w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?resize=300%2C25&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-11.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 418px) 100vw, 418px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/etc\/fstab<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And now simply add Label and file mount point with defaults parameters.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=640%2C241&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1039\" width=\"640\" height=\"241\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?w=812&amp;ssl=1 812w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=300%2C113&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=768%2C288&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-12.png?resize=48%2C18&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption><br><\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to remount everything with <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">mount -a<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"197\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?resize=640%2C197&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1041\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?w=742&amp;ssl=1 742w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?resize=300%2C92&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-13.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aaaaand it&#8217;s all done, &#8220;virtual bro fist&#8221;.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>When we successfully create logical volume and formatted it, as the last thing we need [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":982,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all